examples.en: He hanged for his crimes.
He was hanged for murder.
I am to be hanged in chains.
He was hanged for his crimes.
His tongue is hanged well enough.
The murderer was hanged on Friday.
He hanged himself with a guitar string.
We all were to be hanged upon a gibbet.
Corey hanged himself in his prison cell.
I'll be hanged if I'll give them any money!

As well be hanged for a sheep as (for) a lamb. .
Hanged if I will! *
Hanged if I know! *
The Bouncer hanged up. *
I'll be hanged if I can find it. *
She was hanged if she was going to let them do that. *
Hang on tight!
She hung on his arm.
Don't hang up on me.
This dress hangs well.

The picture hung askew.
He hung a quick U-turn.
Time hangs on his hands.

He hung on her every word.

I said goodbye and hung up.
